            <h2>Why is pair programming important?</h2> Developers on professional teams pair program often because it helps them with test-driven 
            development. Pair programing helps peers catch each others'' errors and mistakes, in addition to helping teams brainstorm on solutions more efficiently.
            
        </p>    
        <img src = "http://asciiville.com/media/comics/asciiville/pair-programming.jpg" alt = "peer programming" >
